race.comment: BUNDELLA (1) gets the nod here following a sharp return over this course and distance 16 days ago. He sat on the speed there and was only beaten 1L at the finish in a Bm65. Lands in a CL2 now with Jones on board and the barrier isn't as bad as it first seemed now following scratchings. Can go one better today. Stablemate LANTAU ISLAND (6) is first-up on the back of just one trial at Deagon. Maloney has been booked for this gelding rather than BUNDELLA despite partnering him last time out. He's a lightly raced gelding with plenty of upside and he's sure to make his presence felt. CORRUPTED (8) usually fires fresh ad he looks ready to go with two trials under her belt in readiness. Can make her presence felt. LIMERO (5) can improve on the first-up effort.
